<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:medium;"><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">Valas Defai</div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.insidiousblood.net/"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-size:x-small;">A member of Insidious Blood</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211027&amp;resize=true" target="top"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-size:xx-small;">My Magelo</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myztic>MyztiC</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Sorcerer<BR>Born-Again Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 1068<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 9:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Sanguine Blade died mostly because they couldn't do anything as a guild. It was always joint effort. And such doesn't elevate the feelings of belonging, achievement and togetherness. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
No, class-only-guilds don't do well, because EQ is designed around class-interdependancy. Only way to make (with those new chat channels) a class-only-guild to work, would to have a server filled with them and then have them forming alliances. But why do that?<br>
<br>
If you want a group of 6 people playing same class (be it wiz, enc, nec, whatever)... you don't need a guild for that, just invite 5 other people of class you're playing and go try it out. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Old wiz, quite a <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.nmnh.si.edu/paleo/dino/">dino</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> :)<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=73401">Myztic Mythoclast</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.archoverseers.org">Arch Overseers</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pickkpockket999>Pickk Pockket999</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 156<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 10:24 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Molto Espresso works so well because bards are such a versatile class. The only other class that could group together would be paladins. I could see a 6 person paladin group working, but not nearly as well as other makeups. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=throes>Throes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Flintnilf the Wise</span><br>  Posts: 254<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/29/03 10:27 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> Still, I would like to see 60 wizards all nuking some POP mobs at the same time<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Sage Flintnilf Ironori<br>
